OL,3,CSister's fight for Infected Blood
OL,4,Cmemorial garden at Chelsea Flower Show
OL,6,F"He was always very much a people
OL,7,Fperson and not with any ego to him,"
OL,8,Fsays his sister Amanda Patton.
OL,10,F"I think this is why everybody loved
OL,11,Fhim. And even though it's nearly 30
OL,12,Fyears since he died, there are a lot
OL,13,Fof people who still remember him,
OL,14,Fwhose lives he touched."
OL,16,FLike thousands of other haemophiliacs,
OL,17,FSimon had been given an infected blood
OL,18,Fproduct, Factor 8, a treatment which
OL,19,Fwas meant to help him.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
