OL,3,CSister's fight for Infected Blood
OL,4,Cmemorial garden at Chelsea Flower Show
OL,6,FBut exhibiting at Chelsea isn't cheap.
OL,7,FThe large show gardens are reliant on
OL,8,Fsponsorship, and she needs to raise
OL,9,Fquarter of a million pounds by the end
OL,10,Fof October.
OL,12,FIf 'Simon's Garden' goes ahead,
OL,13,Felements will then be transported to
OL,14,FSt Bartolph's Church in London,
OL,15,Fcreating a permanent memorial, on
OL,16,Fbehalf not just for her brother, but
OL,17,Fevery haemophiliac whose life was cut
OL,18,Fshort.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
